<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-30T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">813.00/1162: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-30T14:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">December 30,
                                        1921—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 1, 1922—9:48
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>135. Provisional Federal Council issued decrees yesterday convoking
                            Federal Deputies from the three States, and Senators from Honduras and
                            Salvador, in preparatory sessions in the first 15 days of January.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>